JOHANNESBURG – There is a strange but all-too-familiar occurrence of artists whose work becomes more acceptable in countries outside of their own. Yugen Blakrok makes a good example of this phenomenon.
	
	In the wake of the current storm that the Black Panther film is creating, a little unknown fact still remains unnoticed. GALLERY: #BlackPanther opens in SA Among the number of popular SA artist featured on the film's soundtrack there is Yugen Blakrok.
	
	The young beauty from Eastern Cape set down with eNCAs Mbali Langa and gave us an sight to her life philosophies and music as well as how she feels to be part of such a phenomenal project. eNCA